{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"de7dc9cd-da79-4ccb-9a3b-babce012d8d7","content":"No files found in the workspace — so here's the conversion pattern directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe only required change is adding the `xmlns:vm` namespace import and the **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** attribute. Your existing `{Binding ...}` expressions stay the same — the compiler now resolves them at build time instead of at runtime via reflection.\n\n**2. Catch errors at build time** — no extra config needed. With `x:DataType` in place, if you typo a property (e.g. `{Binding Themee}`), you'll get a **build error** like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\n## Key things to know\n\n| Topic | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **Scope** | `x:DataType` cascades to child elements. Set it on the root or on any sub-layout. |\n| **Opt out locally** | Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` on a subtree that binds to a different/unknown type. |\n| **DataTemplates** | Each `DataTemplate` needs its own `x:DataType` — it doesn't inherit from the parent. |\n| **Code-behind** | Still set `BindingContext = new SettingsViewModel();` as before — `x:DataType` only tells the compiler the *expected* type. |\n\nThat's it — one attribute addition gives you compile-time validation of all bindings on the page.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"17b4691b-ca99-487a-96e1-5b858aac167b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no existing files. The user is asking me to show them how to convert a page they have (but haven't provided the files here). I should explain the conversion process and provide example code showing the key changes.\n\nLet me give a concise, practical answer.","outputTokens":615},"id":"ddb29bae-0d41-47f1-8a3f-ac1b3b8a8963","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:58:57.104Z","parentId":"9e72fe2e-bad6-4210-8edf-02d294e83609"}
